2. what is default method
A default method is a method inside an interface that has a body so you can add new methods to an interface without breaking all the classes that already implement it.

3. what is the difference between Predicate, Supplier, Consumer, Function?
    
    All four are built-in functional interfaces in java. The difference is just what they take in and what they return.
    
    Predicate**:** takes something, returns boolean. Used for filtering/checking conditions.
    
    ```java
    Predicate<String> isLong = s -> s.length() > 5;
    System.out.println(isLong.test("hi"));      // false
    System.out.println(isLong.test("Jocelyn")); // true
    ```
    
    Function**:** takes something, returns something (can be a different type). Used for transforming data.
    
    ```java
    Function<String, Integer> getLength = s -> s.length();
    System.out.println(getLength.apply("Jocelyn")); // 7
    ```
    
    Consumer: takes something, returns nothing. Used for side effects like printing or saving.
    
    ```java
    Consumer<String> print = s -> System.out.println("Hello, " + s);
    print.accept("Jocelyn"); // Hello, Jocelyn
    ```
    
    Supplier: takes nothing, returns something. Used for lazy generation or providing values.
    
    ```java
    Supplier<String> getName = () -> "Jocelyn";
    System.out.println(getName.get()); // Jocelyn
    ```
    
